-- American Tourist Killed in Hot-Air Balloon Crash in Switzerland
-- B y   G i l e s   B r o o m
-- 2013-08-06T15:31:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-06/american-tourist-killed-in-hot-air-balloon-crash-in-switzerland.html
A 55-year-old male American tourist
was killed and four other people were injured in a hot-air
balloon accident in the western Swiss Alps, local police said.  The balloon hit a power line near Montbovon about 26
kilometers (16 miles) west of the celebrity resort of Gstaad and
plummeted 50 meters (164 feet), seriously injuring the man’s
wife and two daughters and the pilot, the Fribourg cantonal
police said in a  statement  on their website.  The Swiss Accident Investigation Board is investigating the
crash, according to the statement. The identity of the tourist
killed wasn’t disclosed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Giles Broom in Geneva at 
